article.description: Christian Keeling scored 25 points as Charleston Southern defeated Winthrop 77-63 in the quarterfinals of the Big South Conference Tourney on Thursday. Dontrell Shuler added 22 points for the Buccaneers.
article.headline: Charleston Southern beats Winthrop 77-63 in Big South
article.linkText: Charleston Southern beats Winthrop 77-63 in Big South
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Christian Keeling scored 25 points as Charleston Southern defeated Winthrop 77-63 in the quarterfinals of the Big South Conference Tourney on Thursday. Dontrell Shuler added 22 points for the Buccaneers. Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 16 points for Charleston Southern (17-14). Travis McConico added 11 points, eight rebounds and six assists. Bjorn Broman had 18 points for the Eagles (18-12). Nych Smith added 14 points and six rebounds. Micheal Anumba had 10 points. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
